text: Shaved Piave (Cheese), Tarragon, Pear, Pistachios, Shallot vinaigrette
Choice of Picante, Sopressata, Saucisson Sec (or all three +2)  / Baguette
Horseradish cream cheese, Don Bocarte Anchovy, Toasted Brioche
Bread is sourced from Party Bus Bakery @ 31 Essex Street.
Meat is sourced from Ends Meat @ Essex Market.
Giardineria is sourced from Pickle Guys @ 357 Grand St
Cortese - Checkered tablecloth wine label, classic col fondo frizzante wine. Fresh and easy
Xarel-lo - Xavi planted vines the year his daughter Julia was born. Mineral, crisp
Chenin Blanc - A very Champagne-like sparkler, with density, and a slightly creamy ﬁnish
Macabeo / Xarel-lo / Parellada - Champagne level, from 2015 aged on lees for a long time
Menu Pineau - Moses and Pascal make one thing: Pet-Nats, and they are very good at what they do!
Hárslevelű / Juhfark - Delicious, fresh, funky pet-nat from the legendary volcanic hill, ‘Somló’
Folle Blanche / Pinot Noir / Chardonnay - Classic style dry sparkler. Wet rocks and sea spray
Pinot Auxerrois / Chardonnay - Classy, nice mousse, dry, traditional-style sparkler
Chardonnay - Methode Ancestrale (Pet-Nat) that drinks like a methode traditionelle
Pinot Meunier / Pinot Noir / Chardonnay - Subtle creamy notes, butter and toast, overall very tasty
Chardonnay - Mineral style, with citrus zest and crisp, clean ﬁnish
Cinsault / Aramon - Cyril Cuche in collaboration with Eric Texier, made this tasty, hazy Pet-Nat
Riesling / Pinot Gris - Is it the funkiest Pet-Nat we have? Give it some time open to ﬁnd out
Viognier / Merwah - Something between Pet-Nat and Traditional in style, nice fresh bubbles
Prié Blanc - It’s a grape from the remote region in northern Italy, also the cutest label ever. Frothy fun!
Muscat / Pinot Blanc / Riesling - Fun, hazy frothy Slovenian, very cute label, soft but still zippy
Folle Blanche - With 10% Pinot Noir, which lends a peachy hue to this unﬁltered Pet-Nat
Spergola - Refermentation in bottle, one of the ﬁrst natural frizzante producers. A true classic
Chenin Blanc - When you don’t want to eat dessert, but you want something alittlesweet, this is it
Pinot Noir - From the Pet-Nat masters, 2 years on the lees, fresh strawberries, chalky dry ﬁnish
Nero d’Avola / Mataró / Fiano / Zibibbo / Arneis-Lots of tang and dry zingy red berry fruit, Fun!
Ull de Llebre (Tempranillo) / Moscatel - Bottled with lees, chunky! Floral and red fruited
Pinot Noir - A hit when we poured it by the glass, this is a dry and savory unﬁltered dark pink bubbly
Zibibbo / Fiano / Arneis / Nero d'Avola - A hazy, skinsy, fun Pet-Nat with a psychedelic bunny label
Pinot Gris / Pinot Auxerrois - Amber-hued skin contact Pet-Nat, fresh and grippy
Pinot Noir - A delicious, lighter style sparkling red, stewed fruits in bubble form
Hondarribi Zuri - The zippiest, pickled apple skin, "is this even wine?" fresh, slap-in-the-face white
Albarino - The fresh, “Spring in a bottle,” stony crisp specialty of the Atlantic coast of Spain
Tsolikouri - No skin contact here, just a beautiful white from the mountains in west Georgia
Sauvignon Blanc - A damn good Sancerre, Biodynamic certiﬁed (rare for Sancerre)
Xarel-lo - Tangy and fresh, zippy and thirst quenching, and it’s a liter bottle!
Sauvignon Blanc - A wacky, wild, crisp and fresh natural Sauv Blanc. Both refreshing and mystifying
Domaine des Sanzay, Saumur Blanc ‘Les Bazilles’
Chenin Blanc - A mellow Chenin with good stoniness and balance. Limestone soils, not too ripe
Chardonnay / Pinot Blanc - Freshness from Chard on limestone, density from Pinot Blanc on loam
Riesling / Manzoni Bianco - Dry white with characteristic Lombardy zippiness
Pinot Blanc / Muller-Thurgau / Riesling / Silvaner + more - Wild fun hazy blend from the Brand Bros!
Christian Venier, ‘Les Hauts de Madon’ Blanc
Orbois (Menu Pineau) / Sauvignon Blanc - Round and stony but also a touch tropical.
Vermentino / Pecorino / Ribolla / Falanghina / Moscato / Fiano - Fresh homage to Italian white
Maison Vevey, Blanc de la Salle et Morgex
Prié Blanc - Pure, alpine white from a little village nestled between Switzerland and France
Chenin Blanc - Some might call this the ideal Chenin Blanc. Very charming, dry but ripe
Riesling - Precise, masterfully beautiful dry Riesling. Philip has worked with Uli Stein for many years
Chenin Blanc - From a vineyard of pure stones on top of a cliff. Epic place for an epic Chenin Blanc
Macabeu / Xarel-lo / Parellada / Malvasia and more! - Wild, zippy, with sour beer vibes
Fiano - Pure and delicious, aged in amphoras that are made at the estate with their own clay
Julien Altabar, Bourgogne Blanc ‘La Fleur au Verre’
Chardonnay - Never has a sample that was left here blown more people away. Idyllic natural Chardo
Chenin Blanc - Declassiﬁed Savennieres, absolutely fantastic, dense and slightly creamy Chenin
Eva de los Santos - This is a ridiculously good white for the money! Stony, like Muscadet
Savagnin - A rare vineyard of Savagnin in California provides the fruit for this savory white
Chardonnay / Macabeo / Malvasia / Verdil / Pedro Ximenez - Medium weight, nice evolution
Malvasia de Sitges - Fascinating, slightly oxidative white, with nice density
Lo-Fi Wines, Santa Ynez Valley Chenin
Chenin Blanc - Varietal characteristic with voluptuous weight. A ﬁne California Chenin
Grillo - Unﬁltered, zippy but textured and just right on the freshness level
Jacquère / Altesse - Yellow apple and pear, stone fruit and ﬂowers around a mineral core
Godello - A savory and dense expression with a touch of an oxidative note on the nose
Chardonnay - From young vines of Chardonnay, a perfect introduction to Alice’s whites
Chardonnay - From Alice’s old vines in La Mailloche parcel. Her most iconic white
Procanico / Malvasia - Stone fruit and soft acidity, good clean fun from our friend Joy Kull
Sauvignon Blanc - This is next level Sauv Blanc, creamy and dense, mineral goodness
Moscatel / Semillon / Corinto (Chasselas) - Aromatic with a little white pepper and ﬂeshy texture
Catarratto - A full bodied white, with ample weight, from one of our favorite natural Sicilian producers
80% Menu Pineau (aka Arbois), 20% Romorantin - Truly an aromatic and precise expression
Trebbiano - Viscous and lush, ethereal. Emidio Pepe is like the godfather of Italian natural wine
Sebastien Riffault, Sancerre (several cuvées available)Loire Valley, France
Sauvignon Blanc - We have several of these iconic wines available, ask us if you’d like the rundown
Pinot Noir - Blanc de Noirs, so a white wine from a red grape, aged in oxidative style for 60 months
Pinot Gris - The most delicately light orange wine we have, just a hint of color, stony and easy-going
Roter Veltliner / Grüner Veltliner - Hazy, clean, perfect entry level SC. Between white and orange
Riesling (Alsace) - This has a light touch of skin contact, not amber-hued, more like a skinsy, dry white
Sylvaner / Pinot Blanc / Pinot Auxerrois / Pinot Gris - Super cheerful Alsace blend, light and lithe
Moscatel / Malvasia - Sharp, ﬂoral, and perfumed, very crispy - good for the warm days
Welschriesling / Pinot Gris / Traminer - The rite of passage with orange wine
Chardonnay - It’s Chardo from Chablis, aged in clay amphora with skin contact. Subtle and special
Muscat - Alice makes this wine from Alsatian grapes. Floral, with a tickle on the tongue. Cute cat too!
Pinot Gris / Riesling / Sylvaner - Flavorful, ﬂoral, aromatic and easy-going
Riesling - Dry, with stone fruit and a wild side. Notes of ginger candy, spice and orange blossoms
Gouveio / Viosinho / Malvasia / Rabigato - Delicate, elegant, with creaminess and some grip
Malvasia - Dreamy, lightly aromatic SC. Herbs, tang, and Mediterranean vibe
Sumoll / Xarel-lo Vermell - Mellow, touch of melon, balanced minerals and acid. Yum!
Lledoner Roig / Carinyena Blanca - Lovely, medium-bodied SC. Some fruit, some grip, long ﬁnish
Roussanne / Sauvignon Blanc / Chenin Blanc - From an old co-worker of Eben’s!
Rkatsiteli / Mtsvane - A rare Georgian skin contact that is aged on skins instainless steel, not qvevri
Famoso / Grechetto / Albana - Medium orange, medium tannins, herbs. Nice right down the middle SC
Jacquère - One of the ﬁrst cult wines of the natural wine scene. Delicate, chamomile tea vibes
Altesse - Legendary skin contact from Savoie, dense and balanced
Roussanne / Jacquère / Altesse - A darker, more dried fruit, apricot vibe.
Chasselas / Chardonnay - Fresh and slightly bretty SC from Chile. Nice grip and acid
Malvasia / Ortrugo / Marsanne / Trebbiano - One of the OGs of Italian SC wine, Beautiful zingy nose
Muscat Ottonel - A combination of two vintages, a touch of earl gray over ﬂoral spice and subtle grip
Carignan Blanc - 30 days SC with daily manual punch down, followed by 5 months aging in amphora
Gewurztraminer, Pinot Auxerrois, Muscat - Spicy ﬂoral amber goodness. Classic aromatic Alsace SC
Grechetto / Garganega / Malvasia / Sauvignon / Chardonnay - Benchmark, zippy SC wine
Gewurztraminer / Pinot Gris - Medium-bodied aromatic blend from a natural wine legend
Sauvignon Blanc - One week maceration with only the golden berries
Catarratto - From the "other" Viola, Aldo, apparently more chill and less crazy, like the wine
Chardonnay / Cortese - Some structure here, without deep color or intense dryness. It’s got the grip!
Tardana / Macabeo - Big bold orange with tons of ﬂavor but not tannic or too intense
Malvasia / Santa Soﬁa / Cinguli - A hearty, soulful orange, medium body, with tannic grip and herbs
Pinot Gris - A fan favorite from the by the glass list, nice deep Slovenian SC with some grit and grip
Chenin Blanc / Pinot Gris - Amphora aged Chenin Blanc with a touch of Pinot Gris for color and weight
Khikhvi - Aged in underground Qvevri (pots) for 6 months with skins, in the 8,000 year-old tradition
Pesecká Leánka - Deep amber, fragrant and textured Skin Contact from ancient grape
Bechtold, ‘Comme un Rouge’ Grand Cru Engelberg
Pinot Gris - With long skin contact like a red. Uniquely reddish for an orange wine
Kisi - Resiny, smoky, amber Qvevri wine from Republic of Georgia. Apricots and earth
Ribolla Gialla - An iconic wine from one of the original Friuli orange wine producers
Malvasia, Ortrugo, and Trebbiano Toscano - We love you Elena! Intense and unforgettable
Gamay Noir - Always super light and pretty, like a white wine with a touch of berries
Limnio / Muscat - The Muscat gives ﬂoral aromatics, spice and charm. A nice touch for this Greek rosé
Nerello Mascalese - Odd little rosato that isn't ﬁnished fermenting! A bit tickly, a touch off-dry
Sangiovese / Ciliegiolo - A rosé with perfect density and length
Montepulciano - Unﬁltered, natural, kind of what Susucaru was like back in the day
Nero D’Avola - Perfect, medium bodied rosé, bold but refreshing too
Gamay / Mondeuse / Chardonnay - Co-ferment of white and red grapes. Tasty and stony
Carignan- A happy fruity place in between a dark rosé and a light red. Hi-chew anyone?
Cinsault / Aragon / Muscat - The touch of Muscat gives thisfunkyrosé an extra ﬂoral zing
All the Pinots, Muscat, Gewurz, etc. - Red and white co ferment from Alsace, bright and cosmic!
Dolcetto / Barbera / Nebbiolo / Arneis - A delightful co-ferment from red and white grapes
Debit, Marastina, Plavina, Lasin - Very juicy and tangy chillable red. The wine version of Lite-Brite
Pineau D'Aunis - One of the most classic, vibrant, spicy, prickly versions of this cult grape
Valdiguié - A bright, tart, light red from a grape they thought was Gamay for 100+ years
Pinot Noir - We love a good French Pinot Noir, but this one from Germany is truly delicious
Nerello Mascalese - Very pure, juicy, chillable and unmistakably Nerello Mascalese
Merlot / Garrut / Cabernet Sauvignon - Tangy, tart, playful and fun
Pineau D’Aunis - This is one of the classic wines produced by Loire Valley legend, JP Robinot
Bodegas Gratias, ‘Y Tu de Quien Eres’
Bobal / Sumoll / Local varieties - Funky, pure no nonsense natural red proper for a light chill
Mondeuse - Sometimes a cult natural wine is so good you just have to accept it’s awesome
Gamay - Fully natural vibes, with some dark cherry fruit and earthy funk, from a wise old winemaker
Rossese di Dolceacqua - Northern Italian herbaceous red with a little pep!
Trousseau - Light-medium red from local Jura variety. Soft black cherry fruit, light tannins
Pinot Noir - Special expression from Switzerland. Delicate nose and dark  fruits
Nerello Mascalese / Nerello Cappuccio - Salvo Foti is the OG of Sicilian wines with soul
Listán Negro - From 100+ year-old vines, planted on volcanic soils on Tenerife. Canary funk and spice!
Bobal - A bit more classic, light-medium bodied red, without the tang, but deﬁnitely Partida
Poulsard - One of the most special expressions of the grape, aged in amphora
Cabernet Franc - Super classic, not tannic, not funky, just good ol Cab Franc
Nerello Mascalese- From the 2020 vintage, exhibitingvolcanic Mount Etna elegance
Merlot / Dornfelder - Delicious, savory dark fruited red that is basically a Lambrusco with less bubbles
Barbera / Montepulciano / Aglianico - A tasty, bistrot-style, Italian-inspired red. Bold and easy
Cabernet Franc - When you crave a red that tastes classic, but has a little funk, turn to the Mortiers
Mondeuse - A special, longer maceration red, with a brooding, darker side
Field blend - Tempranillo, with Carignan, Mision and mystery grapes. A vibrant Mexican natural wine
Syrah / Grenache - Modeled after a Cotes du Rhône blend, from Washington State
Côt, Gamay, 10% Gascon - Truly a beautiful wine, vibrant, bright red and dark, meaty fruit.
Tempranillo - Bold, but really fresh and easy going
Cesanese d’Afﬁle - Old vines on volcanic red soil. Delicate bouquet of violets and dark cherries
Cabernet Sauvignon / Merlot - Medium bodied, purple fruited red from just east of Bordeaux
Tempranillo - Low intervention, low sulfur, checks the boxes, and in the end a beautiful classic Rioja
Barbera / Bonarda - Delicious, perfect medium bodied red, silky ﬁnish. Elena, you did it again!
Field blend - 12 varieties from a 100+ year old vineyard on a cliff. Rustic, natural, and singular
Tempranillo - Full bodied and bold, but partial carbonic maceration lends a touch of brightness
Syrah / Grenache / Cinsault - Classic Languedoc red with blackberries proﬁle, and a ‘sauvage’ edge
Malvasia Nera / Negroamaro - A true Calabrian red, with notes of dried herbs and sausage
Baga, Alfrocheiro, Jaen - Rustic and concentrated. Dark violets on contemplative nights.
Cabernet Franc / Côt (Malbec) - Medium-full, darker red with sumptuous dark Loire fruit
Grenache / Syrah / Mourvedre / Carignan - A complex and generous, earthy Southern Rhone red
Malbec - Dark and silky, with good extraction and no new oak ﬂavors
Syrah / Mourvedre / Merlot - Super savory, dark and silky red. Black-fruited and thoroughly satisfying
LARGE FORMAT(all wines are 1.5 Liter unless otherwisenotated)
Sangiovese - Blanc de Noirs style Pet-Nat, hazy, fermented in amphora, pretty damn delicious and fun
Oriol Artigas and Co., ‘3 Porcs’ (Sparkling Rosé)
Cabernet Sauvignon / Merlot / Syrah - Tuets, Frisach and Oriol make one wine together every year.
This time it’s a crazy Pet-Nat, with the lees left in the bottle to develop the bubbles. Chunky!
Sauvignon Blanc - Not your ordinary Sancerre, this one has more weight and fullness to it
Chenin Blanc / Lion de L'oeil - Only thing better than Magic of Juju is a MAG of Magic of Juju!
Corinto (Chasselas) - One of the best Chasselas..es on earth. Slight skin contact, ever-evolving
Vignoble de Rêveur, ‘Un Instant Sur Terre’
Gewurztraminer / Pinot Gris / Riesling - The biggest, tallest bottle of orange wine in the building!
Altura, Isola del Giglio Ansonaco (Skin Contact)
Ansonaco - Thick-skinned grape in the hands of the magical Carfagna family is a pure delight
Malvasia / Moscadella / Catarratto / Nerello Mascalese- from the stoic Frank Cornelissen
Garnacha Tintorera - Cherry and raspberry on the nose and an electric red fruit palate
Pinot / Poulsard / Trousseau / Gamay / Béclans / Enfariné - Wild Jura red if there ever was one
Gamay - Everything we love about Loire Valley Gamay, bright and delicious, with a touch of structure
Carignan / Syrah - One of the originators of the fresh semi-carbo style in Languedoc
Tintilla de Rota - A rare grape that is native to Andalucia. Dark, savory and energetic
Grenache / Carignan - A special, hearty red that Bruno only produces in magnum!
